caption: Okay  tacos but could be cheaper

We met with friends at this place for dinner. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was a winning. we were warmly welcomed by the staff members  and we felt very good. The meal was great. We had a great time and we will visit this place again. Warmly recommended.

(Translated by Google) Excellent food Excellent service The super, super friendly and very familiar staff, they welcome you with a smile and they also say goodbye like that, they make you feel very good Everything is very important, …

This Mexican food spot is a gem hidden inside the mall! The food is really good and the service is great! While it does take about 10-15 min for your order to be ready, they are making the food fresh. I recommend the burritos and nachos. Prices are competitive and a meal will cost ~$8-$12.

The Carne asada burrito is very good. If desired, they add a little hot chili oil to it. Chicken tacos are good, very standard. Al pastor is dry, again very standard for al pastor. Shrimp tostada is just okay, it won't be craved. Food was …

The person who helped me was very nice but the food was horrible. The tortilla didn't even seem like a real tortilla, maybe made of soft plastic, it fell apart, the chicken was super hard, and the had no flavor. Sorry to leave a poor review but this was not worth 11$, or even 1$
